PyTextMiner version 0.4

A simple text miner for CoWord analysis

USAGE
   
   ON LINUX
   
      simply type "python tinaExtract.py" in a the folder where you unzipped PyTextMiner.
         
      it will generate a statistics.zip file containing only statistical data on ngrams
      
      notice that you need Python and Numpy. You can install them safely from your package
      manager by typing:
      
         "sudo apt-get install python-numpy"
          
      in a shell under debian/ubuntu
         
       or
       
         "sudo urpmi python-scipy" 
         
      in a shell on mandriva.

PLATFORMS

   For the moment PyTextMiner was only tested on these Linux platforms:
    
      Linux 64 bits (AMD64) with Python 2.5
      Linux 64 bits (AMD64) with Python 2.6

      Linux 32 bits (i686) with Python 2.5
      Linux 32 bits (i686) with Python 2.6 
 
   However, if you experience problems, see "MANUAL INSTALL" section.
    
MANUAL INSTALL
   For other platforms, PyTextMiner should works if you install:

     - Python 2.6  : http://python.org
      
     - Numpy : http://www.scipy.org/Download

